We awaken in others the same attitude of mind we hold toward them=2E

An unattempted lady could not vaunt of her chastity=2E

Nothing is easier than self-deceit=2E For what each man wishes, that he =
also believes to be true=2E

Modest doubt is called the beacon of the wise=2E

The successful men of action are not sufficiently self-observant to know=
 exactly on what their success depends=2E

The master's eye is the best fertilizer=2E

You traverse the world in search of happiness, which is within the reach=
 of every man=2E A contented mind confers it on all=2E

I am more afraid of an army of 100 sheep led by a lion than an army of 1=
00 lions led by a sheep=2E

Actors often behave like children, and so we're taken for children=2E I =
want to be grown up=2E

Ability without honor is useless=2E

The flowers anew, returning seasons bring! But beauty faded has no secon=
d spring=2E

A man must earnestly want=2E

To me, being an intellectual doesn't mean knowing about intellectual iss=
ues it means taking pleasure in them=2E
